name: Busted!
overview: Suspense, surprises and fun abound in this Korean variety game show featuring big personalities and even bigger mysteries in every episode.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Tackling different mysteries in each episode of this game show, seven sleuths get closer to solving the biggest one of all: What happened to Project D?

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Amateur detectives attempt to untangle a string of mystifying cases, which may be connected to an enigmatic figure known as the Flower Killer.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: With old faces back on the team, the detectives investigate a series of bewildering cases that seem to be linked to a shady organization.

episodes.name: Forewarned Murder
episodes.overview: A man named "M" invites seven people to a murder game party. Among the eight in the room, one will become a victim, and another the culprit.

episodes.name: Treasure Island
episodes.overview: Recognized for their performance, the detectives report to Jeju Island, where their first client asks them to participate in a treasure hunt.

guest_stars.character: Girl on phone in beginning of episode
guest_stars.name: Choi Min-Jae

episodes.name: Kwang-soo, a Murderer
episodes.overview: While enjoying their break on Jeju Island, the detectives get a shocking call from K, who says Kwang-soo is a prime murder suspect and is on the run.

episodes.name: Messages from the Dead
episodes.overview: Jong-min comes across a diary of a dead teen girl who was possibly murdered. To find the truth, he gathers the detectives at the school she attended.

episodes.name: The Last Vampire
episodes.overview: A woman turns up dead on an island off the coast of Incheon. The detectives learn that a centuries-old legend of a vampire has haunted the islanders.

episodes.name: Battle of the Detectives
episodes.overview: To find the missing self-portrait of a recently deceased painter, two rival curators at a Seoul art museum each commission a team of detectives.

episodes.name: The Vanished Magician
episodes.overview: Without any cases to solve, the detectives enjoy watching a magic show rehearsal -- until the show's star magician suddenly disappears without a trace.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Gentleman
episodes.overview: A man who introduces himself as K's old friend offers the detectives lavish pay and a chance to partake in a special mission -- but there's a catch.

episodes.name: Operation: Criminal Transport
episodes.overview: A culprit asks specifically for the detectives to escort him to the police station. In exchange, he promises to tell them everything they want to know.

episodes.name: The Disappearance of K
episodes.overview: The detectives receive a text message from K that was written three months ago. It asks them to come to Incheon, where their final test awaits.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Tackling different mysteries in each episode of this game show, seven sleuths get closer to solving the biggest one of all: What happened to Project D?

episodes.name: Hell of the Gods: Tartarus
episodes.overview: Trapped in individual rooms filled with a variety of challenges, each detective tries to figure out how to escape.

episodes.name: Serial Killing
episodes.overview: The search for K's killer gets complicated when a series of dead bodies are found -- all with a mysterious QR code on them.

episodes.name: Odd Eye: Detective Team vs Phantom Thief
episodes.overview: Hired by a client whose family jewels are in danger of being stolen by a nefarious thief, the detectives hurry to get to it first.

episodes.name: Along with the Gods; The Return of the Genius Detective Team
episodes.overview: When a shaman needs help finding the scattered numbers of a winning lottery ticket, the detectives race against another team for a big reward.

episodes.name: There Lives a Devil
episodes.overview: The team welcomes a new intern, who leads them to a grisly case involving a divorced couple, their son, and a suspicious neighbor who lives next door.

episodes.name: The Curse of the Shaman
episodes.overview: While investigating a suicide, the detectives go to a spooky village, where mysterious things happen to young women -- and outsiders are not welcome.

episodes.name: The Chairman's Secret
episodes.overview: The detectives split up when they're hired by three estranged brothers of a chaebol family -- all eager to find their late father's will.

episodes.name: The Two Clients: The Guys' and Girls' Case Records
episodes.overview: The detectives have fun participating in a crime game show with a K-pop group -- until things get too real.

episodes.name: The 5 Flower Killers
episodes.overview: Eager for more information about the Flower Killer, the team attends an event, where the detectives come across an unexpected death.

episodes.name: The Flower of Death
episodes.overview: Hot on the Flower Killer's trail, the detectives follow a maze of clues from his home to his secret lair, where they learn a shocking truth.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Amateur detectives attempt to untangle a string of mystifying cases, which may be connected to an enigmatic figure known as the Flower Killer.

episodes.name: Share House Food Lupin
episodes.overview: Kwang-soo is back! When a client asks the detectives to uncover which of his roommates is stealing his food, they enter a house filled with secrets.

episodes.name: Detectives Reunited; Two New Cases
episodes.overview: The team splits up to take on two cases: one involving a missing professor, and the other a gory murder inside an illegal gambling den.

episodes.name: The Missing Body
episodes.overview: Investigating the disappearance of a woman's corpse from the morgue, the sleuths encounter a deadly operation with disturbing plans.

episodes.name: Nam Uk-gun and Seonnyeo
episodes.overview: With three women claiming to be his rightful fiancée, a wealthy heir calls on the detectives to deduce which he should marry.

episodes.name: Hostage; The Live
episodes.overview: Following clues from a chilling message and a mysterious USB drive, the team races against time to save a hostage from being killed.

episodes.name: I Just Died
episodes.overview: After receiving a strange letter from a dead man, the detectives look for answers in his hometown - and from his four suspicious friends.

episodes.name: The Ghost Client; The Case of the Imposter Detectives
episodes.overview: A client in need of finding a lost boyfriend contacts the team for help, but they're not the only squad of private eyes who show up to take the case.

episodes.name: The Scale of Destiny
episodes.overview: As the team discovers the truths behind a mysterious organization, they question whether one of their very own could be hiding a dark identity.
